00:01:11.490 --> 00:01:13.610
Geraldine Brooks was born
and raised in Australia

00:01:13.610 --> 00:01:15.330
which accounts for
her lovely accent.

00:01:15.330 --> 00:01:17.350
She came to the US to
complete a masters degree

00:01:17.350 --> 00:01:19.370
at Columbia University
and soon got a job

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:22.520
for the Wall Street Journal
covering conflicts in Africa

00:01:22.520 --> 00:01:24.720 position:56%
and the Balkans and the Middle East.

00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:27.100
That experience provided the
material for her first book,

00:01:27.100 --> 00:01:31.170
Nine Parts of Desire, The
Hidden World of Islamic Women,

00:01:31.170 --> 00:01:33.050
which was an international
best seller.

00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:35.680
Several years later after winning
an overseas press club award

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:38.520
for her coverage of the Gulf
War, she took off the journalist

00:01:38.520 --> 00:01:43.510
and wrote a novel called
Year of Wonders.

00:01:43.510 --> 00:01:46.210
[ Applause ]

00:01:46.210 --> 00:01:47.510
&gt;&gt; Somebody in the
audience just told me

00:01:47.510 --> 00:01:49.510
